### 1. Register a New Customer
POST http://localhost:8082/api/customers/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Alice",
  "lastName": "Client",
  "email": "alice@client.com",
  "passwordHash": "password123",
  "phoneNumber": "+420123456789"
}

### 2. Login (Get Token)
# Use this token in the Authorization header for subsequent requests
POST http://localhost:8082/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@client.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. List All Services
GET http://localhost:8082/api/services

### 4. Find Matching Providers for a Service (e.g., Plumbing ID=1)
GET http://localhost:8082/api/providers/match/1

### 5. Create a Job Request (Booking)
POST http://localhost:8082/api/jobs/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": 1,
  "providerId": 1,
  "serviceId": 1,
  "isUrgent": true,
  "description": "Leaky faucet in the kitchen"
}

### 6. Get Job Status (As Customer)
GET http://localhost:8082/api/jobs/customer/1